  "texts": [
    "This risks selection biases if computational methods rely solely on voluntary self-disclosure of cherry-picked data by platforms.",
    "Over time, major platforms have increasingly restricted third-party researcher access to data through API limitations like Facebook's Ad Library and CrowdTangle analytics tools in 2018, exerting control over data access, limiting transparency, and hampering independent research in the public interest [21,120].The DSA introduces welcome but restrained provisions allowing vetted researchers to access data from VLOPs to analyze systemic risks under Article 40.",
    "However, the exact data types, quantities and protocols remain vague and incomplete.",
    "There are concerns that excessive corporatized control over data access could constrain the efficacy of independent DSA impact analyses [82,109,169].",
    "Therefore, policy evolutions may enable appropriate access to sufficiently detailed, representative data based on the public interest merits of independent research."
